  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the Reinsertion and Reintegration of Former Combatants in Bangui, Bria and Kaga Bandoro in Central African Republic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM supports the Central African Republic Government through the National Disengagement, Disassociation, Reintegration, and Reconciliation (DDRR) Program (UEPNDDRR, for its French acronym) in the implementation of socio-economic reintegration and reinsertion activities for former combatants, as well as vulnerable/at-risk youth in various regions of the country. This project contributes to the socio-economic reintegration of former combatants into their communities of origin through resocialization activities, vocational training, monitoring and technical assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
